      "source": [
        "## Fast Style Transfer"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "RSxqiKcapLDJ"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "import tensorflow_hub as hub\n",
        "import tensorflow as tf\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "from PIL import Image\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "\n",
        "# Load model from TF Hub\n",
        "model = hub.load('https://tfhub.dev/google/magenta/arbitrary-image-stylization-v1-256/2')\n",
        "\n",
        "# Load content and style images\n",
        "def load_image(path, max_dim=512):\n",
        "    img = Image.open(path).convert('RGB')\n",
        "    img = img.resize((max_dim, max_dim))\n",
        "    img = np.array(img) / 255.0\n",
        "    img = tf.convert_to_tensor(img, dtype=tf.float32)\n",
        "    return tf.image.resize_with_pad(img, max_dim, max_dim)[tf.newaxis, :]\n",
        "\n",
        "#content_path = \"/content/image_converted.jpg\"\n",
        "#style_path = \"/content/ChatGPT Image May 11, 2025, 11_07_22 AM.png\"\n",
        "\n",
        "style_path = \"/content/Mona_Lisa,_by_Leonardo_da_Vinci,_from_C2RMF_retouched.jpg.webp\"\n",
        "content_path = \"/content/ChatGPT Image May 11, 2025, 11_07_22 AM.png\"\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "content_image = load_image(content_path)\n",
        "style_image = load_image(style_path)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Stylize\n",
        "stylized_image = model(tf.constant(content_image), tf.constant(style_image))[0]\n",
        "\n",
        "# Save or display\n",
        "def show(img, title=''):\n",
        "    plt.imshow(tf.squeeze(img))\n",
        "    plt.title(title)\n",
        "    plt.axis('off')\n",
        "    plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "show(content_image, \"Content\")\n",
        "show(style_image, \"Style\")\n",
        "show(stylized_image, \"Stylized Output\")\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {

      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## Classic NST"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "xrVEJgT8pSEn"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "oariW6__TY-3"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# ✅ STEP 1: Install & Import\n",
        "import tensorflow as tf\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "import PIL.Image\n",
        "import time\n",
        "import functools\n",
        "\n",
        "# ✅ STEP 2: Load Images & Preprocess\n",
        "def load_img(path_to_img):\n",
        "    max_dim = 512\n",
        "    img = tf.io.read_file(path_to_img)\n",
        "    img = tf.image.decode_image(img, channels=3)\n",
        "    img = tf.image.convert_image_dtype(img, tf.float32)\n",
        "\n",
        "    shape = tf.cast(tf.shape(img)[:-1], tf.float32)\n",
        "    long_dim = max(shape)\n",
        "    scale = max_dim / long_dim\n",
        "\n",
        "    new_shape = tf.cast(shape * scale, tf.int32)\n",
        "\n",
        "    img = tf.image.resize(img, new_shape)\n",
        "    img = img[tf.newaxis, :]\n",
        "    return img\n",
        "\n",
        "def imshow(image, title=None):\n",
        "    if len(image.shape) > 3:\n",
        "        image = tf.squeeze(image, axis=0)\n",
        "    plt.imshow(image)\n",
        "    if title:\n",
        "        plt.title(title)\n",
        "\n",
        "\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Upload your images or provide paths\n",
        "content_path = \"/content/ChatGPT Image May 11, 2025, 11_07_22 AM.png\"\n",
        "style_path = \"/content/image_converted.jpg\"\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "content_image = load_img(content_path)\n",
        "style_image = load_img(style_path)\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "# ✅ STEP 3: Load Pretrained VGG19\n",
        "vgg = tf.keras.applications.VGG19(include_top=False, weights='imagenet')\n",
        "vgg.trainable = False\n",
        "\n",
        "# ✅ STEP 4: Define Layers\n",
        "content_layers = ['block5_conv2']\n",
        "style_layers = [\n",
        "    'block1_conv1',\n",
        "    'block2_conv1',\n",
        "    'block3_conv1',\n",
        "    'block4_conv1',\n",
        "    'block5_conv1'\n",
        "]\n",
        "num_content_layers = len(content_layers)\n",
        "num_style_layers = len(style_layers)\n",
        "\n",
        "# ✅ STEP 5: Feature Extractor Model\n",
        "def vgg_layers(layer_names):\n",
        "    outputs = [vgg.get_layer(name).output for name in layer_names]\n",
        "    model = tf.keras.Model([vgg.input], outputs)\n",
        "    return model\n",
        "\n",
        "style_extractor = vgg_layers(style_layers)\n",
        "content_extractor = vgg_layers(content_layers)\n",
        "\n",
        "# ✅ STEP 6: Gram Matrix for Style\n",
        "def gram_matrix(input_tensor):\n",
        "    result = tf.linalg.einsum('bijc,bijd->bcd', input_tensor, input_tensor)\n",
        "    input_shape = tf.shape(input_tensor)\n",
        "    num_locations = tf.cast(input_shape[1]*input_shape[2], tf.float32)\n",
        "    return result / num_locations\n",
        "\n",
        "# ✅ STEP 7: Style Content Model\n",
        "class StyleContentModel(tf.keras.models.Model):\n",
        "    def __init__(self, style_layers, content_layers):\n",
        "        super().__init__()\n",
        "        self.vgg = vgg_layers(style_layers + content_layers)\n",
        "        self.vgg.trainable = False\n",
        "        self.style_layers = style_layers\n",
        "        self.content_layers = content_layers\n",
        "\n",
        "    def call(self, inputs):\n",
        "        inputs = inputs * 255.0\n",
        "        preprocessed_input = tf.keras.applications.vgg19.preprocess_input(inputs)\n",
        "        outputs = self.vgg(preprocessed_input)\n",
        "        style_outputs, content_outputs = (outputs[:len(self.style_layers)],\n",
        "                                          outputs[len(self.style_layers):])\n",
        "        style_outputs = [gram_matrix(style_output) for style_output in style_outputs]\n",
        "        content_dict = {content_name: value\n",
        "                        for content_name, value in zip(self.content_layers, content_outputs)}\n",
        "        style_dict = {style_name: value\n",
        "                      for style_name, value in zip(self.style_layers, style_outputs)}\n",
        "        return {'content': content_dict, 'style': style_dict}\n",
        "\n",
        "extractor = StyleContentModel(style_layers, content_layers)\n",
        "\n",
        "# ✅ STEP 8: Define Loss Functions\n",
        "style_targets = extractor(style_image)['style']\n",
        "content_targets = extractor(content_image)['content']\n",
        "\n",
        "image = tf.Variable(content_image)\n",
        "\n",
        "style_weight = 1e-2\n",
        "content_weight = 1e4\n",
        "\n",
        "def style_content_loss(outputs):\n",
        "    style_outputs = outputs['style']\n",
        "    content_outputs = outputs['content']\n",
        "    style_loss = tf.add_n([\n",
        "        tf.reduce_mean((style_outputs[name] - style_targets[name])**2)\n",
        "        for name in style_outputs.keys()\n",
        "    ])\n",
        "    style_loss *= style_weight / num_style_layers\n",
        "\n",
        "    content_loss = tf.add_n([\n",
        "        tf.reduce_mean((content_outputs[name] - content_targets[name])**2)\n",
        "        for name in content_outputs.keys()\n",
        "    ])\n",
        "    content_loss *= content_weight / num_content_layers\n",
        "    return style_loss + content_loss\n",
        "\n",
        "# ✅ STEP 9: Optimizer & Training Step\n",
        "@tf.function()\n",
        "def train_step(image):\n",
        "    with tf.GradientTape() as tape:\n",
        "        outputs = extractor(image)\n",
        "        loss = style_content_loss(outputs)\n",
        "\n",
        "    grad = tape.gradient(loss, image)\n",
        "    opt.apply_gradients([(grad, image)])\n",
        "    image.assign(tf.clip_by_value(image, 0.0, 1.0))\n",
        "\n",
        "# ✅ STEP 10: Run Style Transfer\n",
        "opt = tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=0.02)\n",
        "epochs = 5\n",
        "steps_per_epoch = 10\n",
        "\n",
        "start = time.time()\n",
        "\n",
        "for n in range(epochs):\n",
        "    for m in range(steps_per_epoch):\n",
        "        train_step(image)\n",
        "    print(f\"Epoch {n+1} completed\")\n",
        "\n",
        "end = time.time()\n",
        "print(f\"Total time: {end - start:.1f} sec\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# ✅ STEP 11: Show Final Result\n",
        "imshow(image.read_value(), \"Stylized Image\")"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 695
        },
        "id": "ULGJE8S9UC1T",
        "outputId": "b785338c-d58c-4436-c018-a707156b3000"
      },

      "source": [
        "# STEP: Convert and save final image\n",
        "def tensor_to_image(tensor):\n",
        "    tensor = tensor * 255\n",
        "    tensor = tf.clip_by_value(tensor, 0, 255)\n",
        "    tensor = tf.cast(tensor[0], tf.uint8)\n",
        "    return Image.fromarray(tensor.numpy())\n",
        "\n",
        "# Convert to PIL image\n",
        "stylized_image = tensor_to_image(image)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Save to disk\n",
        "stylized_image.save(\"/content/stylized_output.jpg\")\n",
        "print(\"✅ Stylized image saved at /content/stylized_output.jpg\")\n"
      ],
